@k4yt3x Sounds great ! Out of curiosity, how did you implement it ? Another problem I had was that because of video compression, identical frames were not bit-perfect copies, meaning that their hash could not be used to identify them. (Thus the need of mpdecimate.)

Also, is _ffprobe_ still used in 5.0 for getting the number of frames ? If so, do you think it would be possible to port my fix for using _ffmpeg_ instead ?

Thanks for your great work ! Getting frame interpolation would be awesome, but I hope that project like [AnimeInterp](https://github.com/lisiyao21/AnimeInterp) will keep development ongoing, because other interpolation algorithms like RIFE did not give satisfying results when I tried them.
